<%# A one-time, non-blocking courtesy notice. We only set strictly-necessary
    cookies (login session, CSRF) plus two preference cookies — theme and the
    remembered feed filter — none for tracking — so no consent is required; an
    Accept/Reject wall would be theater. Hence a plain notice with a single
    dismiss, not a consent gate.

    Hidden by default; the controller reveals it on first visit and remembers the
    dismissal in localStorage — deliberately NOT a cookie, so the copy's "exactly
    three cookies" stays literally true. %>
<aside class="cookie-notice" data-controller="cookie-notice" aria-label="<%= t('cookie_notice.label') %>" hidden>
  <p class="cookie-notice__text">
    <span class="ph ph-cookie cookie-notice__icon" aria-hidden="true"></span> <%= t('cookie_notice.body') %>
  </p>
  <button type="button" class="button-small primary" data-action="cookie-notice#dismiss">
    <%= t('cookie_notice.dismiss') %>
  </button>
</aside>
